Class AbstractBigDecimalAggregate

    public abstract class AbstractBigDecimalAggregate
extends Object
implements Aggregate<BigDecimal>
    Base class for Aggregate funtions that handle BigDecimal precision values. The addValue(Number) method ensures that the given Number is transformed into a BigDecimal before calling the doAddValue(BigDecimal).

      • addValue

        public boolean addValue(Number value)
        Ensures that the Number is transformed to a BigDecimal and before doAddValue(BigDecimal) is called. The transformation logic is:
        • If the Number is an instance of BigDecimal the casted instance will be passed to doAddValue(BigDecimal).
        • If the Number is an instance of BigInteger a new BigDecimal is created and the BigInteger is passed to the BigDecimal.BigDecimal(BigInteger)'s constructor
      • In any other case the Number is interpreted as a double value and a new BigDecimal is created with that double value.
Specified by:
addValue in interface Aggregate<BigDecimal>
Parameters:
value - the value to add.
Returns:
true if the Aggregate.addValue(Number) operation changed the value of this Aggregate.
Since:
1.2.0;
